    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>' $X$ ' is a polymer, which is mainly used for making unbreakable cups and laminated sheets. The monomers of ' $X$ ' are</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>urea and formaldehyde</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>ethylene glycol and phthalic acid</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>phenol and formaldehyde</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>1,3-butadiene and styrene</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><strong>Given:</strong></p>\n<p>Polymer <strong>‘X’</strong> is mainly used for making <strong>unbreakable cups</strong> and <strong>laminated sheets</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>We’re asked:</strong> What are the <strong>monomers</strong> of polymer X?</p>\n\n<h3>Step 1: Identify the polymer</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Unbreakable cups</strong> and <strong>laminated sheets</strong> are typically made from <strong>melamine-formaldehyde</strong> or <strong>phenol-formaldehyde</strong> type resins.</p></li>\n<li><p>However, <strong>phenol-formaldehyde resin</strong> (commonly known as <strong>Bakelite</strong>) is specifically known for:</p></li>\n<li><p>Being <strong>hard and brittle</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Used in <strong>electrical switches</strong>, <strong>unbreakable crockery</strong>, <strong>laminated sheets</strong>, etc.</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Step 2: Match with monomers</h3>\n<p>Bakelite (phenol-formaldehyde resin) is formed by:</p>\n<p>$ \\text{Phenol} + \\text{Formaldehyde} \\longrightarrow \\text{Phenol-formaldehyde resin (Bakelite)} $</p>\n<p>Hence, the monomers are <strong>phenol</strong> and <strong>formaldehyde</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3>✅ <strong>Correct Answer:</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Option C:</strong> phenol and formaldehyde</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "tg-eapcet-2025-online-2nd-may-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
