    "explanation": "<p>All the given statements are correct i.e. $A, B, C$.</p>\n<p>Glyptal is made from monomer ethylene glycol and phthalic acid.</p>\n<ul><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2023 (Online) 13th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Polymers Question 5 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ml5qcmcr/95bff296-c69e-4865-82a6-37a35e4fce73/ea236fb0-0084-11f1-8644-5729a87cc316/file-jaoe38c1ml5qcmcs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ml5qcmcr/95bff296-c69e-4865-82a6-37a35e4fce73/ea236fb0-0084-11f1-8644-5729a87cc316/file-jaoe38c1ml5qcmcs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2023 (Online) 13th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Polymers Question 5 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ml5qcnl7/afbafaeb-9f00-4220-914f-67ea1088ff40/eb1793b0-0084-11f1-8644-5729a87cc316/file-jaoe38c1ml5qcnl8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ml5qcnl7/afbafaeb-9f00-4220-914f-67ea1088ff40/eb1793b0-0084-11f1-8644-5729a87cc316/file-jaoe38c1ml5qcnl8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">\n\n<li><p>Bakelite is used in making combs, phonograph records, electrical switches and handles of utensils etc.</p></li>\n\n<li><p>Nylon-2-nylon-6 is an alternating polyamide copolymer of glycine and amino caproic acid.</p></li>\n\n</ul>\n<p>It is a biodegradable polymer.</p>",
