    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct match is A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II.</p>\n<p>Bakelite is a polymer made up of monomers, phenol and formaldehyde.</p>\n<p>Natural rubber is a polymer made up of monomers 2 -methyl-1,3-butadiene.</p>\n<p>Glyptal is formed from monomeric units phthalic acid and ethylene glycol.</p>\n<p>Nylon-2-nylon-6 is formed from glycine and aminocaproic acid monomers.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2023-online-12th-may-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Amongst the following, how many of them come under the category of elastomers?\nNatural rubber, polyethene, vulcanized rubber, bakelite, polyvinylchloride, buna-N, nylon-6, neoprene\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "4"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "5"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "3"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "6"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Let's analyze the list one by one to identify which ones are elastomers:</p>\n\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Natural rubber}$$ – It is a classic elastomer, mainly composed of cis-1,4-polyisoprene.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Polyethene}$$ – This is a thermoplastic polymer, not known for rubber-like elasticity.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Vulcanized rubber}$$ – Vulcanization is a process applied to rubber (often natural rubber) to enhance its elasticity and strength, so it remains an elastomer.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Bakelite}$$ – This is a thermosetting plastic, not an elastomer.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Polyvinylchloride (PVC)}$$ – Typically a thermoplastic, it does not exhibit the high elasticity characteristic of elastomers.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Buna-N}$$ – Also known as nitrile rubber, it is a synthetic elastomer commonly used for its oil resistance.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Nylon-6}$$ – A polyamide that is a thermoplastic, not classified as an elastomer.</p></p>\n<p><p>$$\\textbf{Neoprene}$$ – Another synthetic rubber well known for its elastic properties, making it an elastomer.</p></p>\n\n<p>From the list, the elastomers are:</p>\n\n<p><p>Natural rubber</p></p>\n<p><p>Vulcanized rubber</p></p>\n<p><p>Buna-N</p></p>\n<p><p>Neoprene</p></p>\n\n<p>Thus, there are 4 elastomers.</p>\n<p>The correct answer is: Option A (4).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ts-eamcet-2023-online-12th-may-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
